<hl>
<seg id=1> China will speed up the market system for training more qualified people. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Beijing, September 1st - Recently the Politic Bureau of the Central Committee of Government Administrative Affairs and the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of Human Resources sent out a notice that they want markets for more qualified people enhanced, speeding up the development of the market for more highly skilled people, and intensifying healthy development of the market for qualified people. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The directive pointed out that the whole goals of training and developing a market for qualified people: To achieve freedom for people to choose their careers and for companies to choose suitable employees.  To achieve a balanced market between having enough qualified people and companies needs for qualified people. To improve service for the society and to improve the benefits to society.  To make this market of qualified people play a fundamental role in the management of human resources. </seg>
<seg id=4> The short term goal of training and developing the market for qualified people: in two or three years to draw up basic policies and regulations for the needs of  operating this market for qualified people, in the medium and larger cities offices should be set up for operating the market for qualified people.  The local information network for qualified people should be constructed and developed, assist in the development of professional people for this market.  Build regional markets for qualified people. </seg>
<seg id=5> Before the year 2000, the nationwide basic market system for qualified people should be in place so that that market is functioning as planned to give guidance and provide professional services. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The Government Department of State Human Resources wants all levels of local human resources offices to intensify the developing and management of this market for qualifying people for this Market and enhance the research and regulations for this Market, identify a strategy for implementing this plan for developing this Market, gradually building up and perfecting the Market system for qualified people, taking into account local needs and local guidance. </seg>
</p>
